  <refbody>

    <section id="recommended-layout">
      <title>Recommended repository layout</title>
      <p>A layout that scales to real teams:</p>
      <codeblock>repo/
  dita/
    maps/
    topics/
  plugins/
    com.yourco.html5.custom/
      plugin.xml
      xsl/
      resources/
  build/
    ditaval/
    *.properties
  .github/
    workflows/
  out/  (gitignored)</codeblock>
      <p>This supports:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>versioned build settings</li>
        <li>filter variants</li>
        <li>portable plug-ins</li>
        <li>CI pipelines</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="ditaval-variants">
      <title>Build variants with DITAVAL filtering</title>
      <p>DITAVAL files define conditional processing rules for attributes like <codeph>audience</codeph>, <codeph>platform</codeph>, or custom props.</p>
      <p>Example <codeph>build/ditaval/web.ditaval</codeph>:</p>
      <codeblock outputclass="language-xml">&lt;val&gt;
  &lt;prop action="exclude" att="platform" val="print"/&gt;
&lt;/val&gt;</codeblock>
      <p>Build:</p>
      <codeblock outputclass="language-bash">dita -i dita/maps/book.ditamap -f html5 -o out/html5-web --args.filter=build/ditaval/web.ditaval</codeblock>
      <p>Store common settings in <codeph>build/html5.properties</codeph> and override only filter + output per variant.</p>
    </section>

  </refbody>
